I"\<p>The first equation on p. 1051 of Stewart (2009) should read</p>

<p>$1/[1+(1/d-1)^T]$</p>

<p>instead of</p>

<p>$1/[1+(1-1/d)^T]$</p>

<p>The second equation on p. 1051 should read</p>

<p>$\sum_{i=0}^{T-1}\frac{(T+i-1)!}{i!(T-1)!} ~ p_A^T p_b^i$</p>

<p>instead of</p>

<p>$\sum_{i=0}^{T-1}\frac{(T-i-1)!}{i!(T-1)!} ~ p_A^T p_b^i$</p>

<p>Stewart, N. (2009). Decision by sampling: The role of the decision environment in risky choice. <em>Quarterly Journal of Experimental Psychology, 62,</em> 1041â€“1062. <a href="https://doi.org/10.1080/17470210902747112">doi: 10.1080/17470210902747112</a></p>

